How could it not be?

114
00:07:02,583 --> 00:07:05,166
Our feelings for each
other are all we have.

115
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,666
[CHIAKI] For a supposed
emotional affair,

116
00:07:08,750 --> 00:07:10,458
you sure know a lot of details.

117
00:07:13,708 --> 00:07:15,291
That's because I, um...

118
00:07:15,375 --> 00:07:17,125
I read Kanade's diary.

119
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:21,958
[MAFUYU] Disgusting!
Reading someone else's diary?

120
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,583
You suck, Kaho!

121
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:26,750
I know. I'm the worst.

122
00:07:26,833 --> 00:07:29,375
Hey, there.
So, look, Mafuyu...

123
00:07:29,458 --> 00:07:31,083
Thanks for the free show.

124
00:07:31,166 --> 00:07:32,250
[MAFUYU gasps]

125
00:07:32,916 --> 00:07:35,166
But isn't that the
landlord's underwear?

126
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:36,750
I'd say you suck.

127
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:38,541
You're the one
wearing stolen skivvies!

128
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:39,750
Yeah, yeah...

129
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:41,916
I know. I totally suck.

130
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,958
But still... at least
I don't read diaries.

131
00:07:45,041 --> 00:07:47,500
Diaries contain the
hearts of their owners.

132
00:07:47,583 --> 00:07:51,000
You can peep into a bathroom,
but you can't peep into a heart!

133
00:07:51,083 --> 00:07:52,875
So many things are better!

134
00:07:52,958 --> 00:07:55,666
You can strain your ears
to appropriately eavesdrop,

135
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:57,250
stand guard while he's bathing,

136
00:07:57,333 --> 00:07:59,291
drink his bathwater
to stay healthy,

137
00:07:59,375 --> 00:08:01,000
sniff the shoes
he's just taken off,

138
00:08:01,083 --> 00:08:03,541
swap your chopsticks for
his when he's not looking,

139
00:08:03,625 --> 00:08:06,166
take his old toothbrush out of
the trash so you can use it,

140
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:07,333
gather his hair...

141
00:08:07,416 --> 00:08:10,125
[DAIKOKU]
I understand... all too well!

142
00:08:10,208 --> 00:08:13,250
When you love someone too much,
you want everything of theirs.

143
00:08:14,791 --> 00:08:17,625
Like chewed gum as
well as used tissues.

144
00:08:17,708 --> 00:08:20,083
Anything they've
touched is holy.

145
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:22,708
I don't know about him.
I really don't.

146
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:26,291
The point is, my dear...

147
00:08:26,375 --> 00:08:27,750
You need not feel bad or guilty

148
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:30,666
for merely peeking
at that boy's diary.

149
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:32,000
What child's play!

150
00:08:32,083 --> 00:08:33,208
A diary?

151
00:08:33,291 --> 00:08:35,166
Why, I check your mail
and phone messages,

152
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:37,583
and I do that every
day without fail!

153
00:08:37,666 --> 00:08:38,916
[KAHO]
Daikoku...

154
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,958
Is that, by chance, my phone?

155
00:08:41,041 --> 00:08:42,625
Wait--you unlocked it?

156
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:47,000
You're even writing back as me?

157
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:48,291
Daikoku...

158
00:08:48,375 --> 00:08:50,750
Stop it! Give me back my phone!

159
00:08:52,875 --> 00:08:54,375
[SHUGO]
Kanade!

160
00:08:54,458 --> 00:08:56,458
The sports festival is tomorrow?

161
00:08:56,541 --> 00:08:58,583
Why didn't you tell me
about this earlier?!

162
00:08:58,666 --> 00:09:00,833
Hey! How'd you get
my paper airplane?

163
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:02,875
[SHUGO] I want you to think
about what you've done.

164
00:09:02,958 --> 00:09:04,916
How many times have
I told you not to fold

165
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,833
important handouts
into paper airplanes?

166
00:09:06,916 --> 00:09:07,833
[KANADE]
I can't hear you!

167
00:09:07,916 --> 00:09:10,125
Well, shoot. Now what?

168
00:09:10,208 --> 00:09:13,166
I've got that trip tomorrow with
the neighborhood association.

169
00:09:13,250 --> 00:09:14,750
[KANADE]
No way!

170
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:17,333
What am I gonna do about lunch
for the sports festival, then?

171
00:09:17,416 --> 00:09:18,625
I hate this!

172
00:09:18,708 --> 00:09:20,500
I'll be so hungry
after all those games,

173
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:21,916
but no food for me!

174
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,291
Aw, man... Boo.

175
00:09:23,375 --> 00:09:25,666
[SHUGO] It might be
difficult so last minute,

176
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:27,958
but I'll see if I can
get out of the trip.

177
00:09:28,041 --> 00:09:30,208
I could just make
you a boxed lunch,

178
00:09:30,291 --> 00:09:33,583
but you'd still have to eat
it all by yourself, poor guy.

179
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:35,583
It's fine. Go on your trip.

180
00:09:35,666 --> 00:09:37,500
Besides, this is my fault.

181
00:09:37,583 --> 00:09:39,541
[KAHO]
Um... If you want...

182
00:09:39,625 --> 00:09:40,375
I could maybe go--

183
00:09:40,458 --> 00:09:41,541
I can go with him.

184
00:09:41,625 --> 00:09:42,625
[SHUGO]
Taga?!

185
00:09:42,708 --> 00:09:44,583
For real?! You'd do that?

186
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:48,333
I always end up
going to watch anyway.

187
00:09:48,416 --> 00:09:50,541
We all do.
Gotta cheer you on, right?

188
00:09:50,625 --> 00:09:52,500
[SHUGO]
On your day off, no less!

189
00:09:52,583 --> 00:09:53,750
[KOTA]
And every year,

190
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:55,958
